context: George Brown College offers diploma, advanced diploma, graduate certificate programs, and online postgraduate certificates in Human Resources. The programs reflect current industry trends and prepare students to work towards obtaining professional designations offered through the Human Resources Professionals Association (HRPA). HRPA designation framework and requirements are subject to change and students are advised to check HRPA website regularly. The human resources programs enable students to gain real world experience through field education and hands-on research projects. George Brown College's School of Human Resources has been recognized with a reader's choice award by Canadian HR Reporter.
